The paper deals with algorithms for representing the shape of unorganised point clouds, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithms also involve graph theory and topology, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
